(16, 1, '2018-06-14 08:57:42', '2018-06-14 08:57:42', '(rewrite in first-person)\r\n<h3>Background</h3>\r\nThe Liberty Bank Building is a community development built in the Central District (CD), on 24th &amp; Union st. This project is a unique and diverse partnership of many community members and groups that work together to make affordable housing more accessible to individuals, groups and families who are susceptible to the consequences of rapid urban development occurring in the CD.\r\n<h3>Design Problem &amp; Project Goals</h3>\r\nCurrent information about the leasing process for the Liberty Bank Building is complex, lengthy, and inaccessible to individuals most in need of this very information. Consequently, there has been misinformation spreading about how the application process works for the Liberty Bank Building.\r\n\r\nThe project goals are to clarify the eligibility requirements for affordable housing, explain the application process for leasing at the Liberty Bank Building, and affirmatively target audiences affected by rapidly rising rent in the CD. This will be achieved through a leasing packet design that is intuitive and\r\nsimply explains the affordable housing application process, and will include the following deliverables:\r\n<h3>Deliverables</h3>\r\n(a single packet of the following items)\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Overview / timeline document, (similar to the one produced by NY Housing Connect )</li>\r\n 	<li>FAQs document</li>\r\n 	<li>General leasing flyer with building features, photos, location map, and income requirements</li>\r\n 	<li>Income limit sheet (similar to the one produced by NY Housing Connect )</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Successes &amp; Failures</h3>\r\n<h4>Audience</h4>\r\n<h5>Primary</h5>\r\nIndividuals and families living in the CD who qualify for affordable housing and those who are looking for clear information on the leasing process and how to apply for the Liberty Bank Building affordable housing units.\r\n<h5>Secondary</h5>\r\nCommunity members and small businesses, particularly of pan-african decent, affected by displacement in the CD; or those individuals and community partners at risk of being unable to afford rapid rent increases in the CD’s housing and commercial real estate market.\r\n<h4>Relationships</h4>\r\n<h5>Client – LBB Building Partners</h5>\r\nThe Capitol Hill Housing Association ensures their approach to each community building is both intentional and affective in targeting individuals in need of affordable housing. For this project the Liberty Bank Partners _____.\r\n(something about how this collateral strengthened the LBB partners trust in CHH’s ability to be aware of its context and deliver content that is relevant to this project’s audience).\r\n<h5>Client – Designer</h5>\r\nThe client will primarily be a resource for information, questions, and any background material required for the designer to create the requested deliverables. The client and their affiliates will also serve as a\r\ncritical observer of all copy and design material. The client will share responsibility in previewing the copy and designed deliverables throughout the design process, including critical points in the timeline\r\nlike presentations and check-ins. Communications will be carried out over email, phone, and in person.\r\n<h3>The Impact</h3>\r\n*** EDIT ***', 'The Liberty Bank Building', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-liberty-bank-building__trashed', '', '', '2018-07-07 02:28:55', '2018-07-07 02:28:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/?p=16', 0, 'post', '', 0),
