(62, 1, '2018-06-30 02:01:30', '2018-06-30 02:01:30', 'Capitol Hill Housing (CHH) is a public corporation organized by the City of Seattle. Their mission is to build vibrant and engaged communities through affordable housing and community development. They own and manage 48 affordable properties throughout the Seattle area, serving low- and moderate-income residents and work to improve neighborhoods for all of Seattle since 1976.\r\n<h2>The Resident Services Department</h2>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Resident Services at Capitol Hill Housing exists to provide its residents with community resources, referrals to supportive services, and community support for each building and property.</span>\r\n<h3>Design problems</h3>\r\n<h4>Awareness</h4>\r\nThe Senior Communications Manager at CHH, Ashwin Warrior, contacted me in need of some brand collateral development for the Resident Services department. After a completing a survey of property residents, CHH found that a majority of residents were not aware that CHH offers additional services through their Resident Service Coordinators. We presumed this lack of awareness was in part due to their inconsistent templates and methods used to reaching residents.\r\n<h4>Accessibility and Consistency</h4>\r\nAnother concern Ashwin approached me about was their reliance on Microsoft Word templates. This was a problem because these same templates were being used by other City government entities, like the Public Library. This overlap in branding between government agencies clouded the CHH brand and was a key factor in CHH wanting to unify their brand image and messaging in order to stand up for the community.\r\n\r\nResident Services Coordinators (RSC) are the central resource for residents living in CHH properties. RSC’s will help residents with anything from answering a community question, hosting a community event, to receiving need based services like rental assistance, live-in health care, transportation services, and much more.\r\n\r\nGiven the broad scope of services and experience, it was paramount to create a templates that anyone could open and use on any computer, without much knowledge of typography and design layout, while still creating something unique to their community building and consistent with the larger CHH brand. These templates needed to be easily accessible/editable, simply formatted, and customizable for RSC’s to implement in each of their unique communities.\r\n<h3>Existing Collateral</h3>\r\nAshwin outlined five key collateral items the RSC\'s used most:\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n[scroller]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-32 size-large" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/poster_resident-services-e1530318746544-834x1024.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="786" /><img class="alignnone wp-image-34 size-large" style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tmpl_individual-rsc-768x1024.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="853" />[/scroller]\r\n<h4>Information and Welcome Sheets</h4>\r\nA general welcome sheet given new residents that informs them about Capitol Hill Housing (CHH) and the resources that are available to them through the Resident Services program, and a Resident Service Coordinator (RSC) welcome sheet that introduces the individual RS Coordinator for the resident\'s property. Both these documents are provided to new residents upon moving in. It includes essential resources in addition to CHH and RSC\'s contact information.\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-35 size-large" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tmpl_residence-calendar-e1530319018147-1024x803.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="502" />\r\n<h4>Monthly Event Calendar</h4>\r\nA monthly calendar specific to each building property that shows all events and key date for the property residents to be aware of. The monthly calendars are posted on community boards in public building spaces.\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-33 size-large" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tmpl_event-flyers-e1530319332673-797x1024.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="822" />\r\n<h4>Event Flyers</h4>\r\nEvent flyers are posted in community spaces to advertise for major events. RSC\'s also create print-off half-sheet handouts for local, building specific events, and are posted in building community spaces and on residency doors.\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-36 size-large" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tmpl_resource-one-sheet-e1530319531779-819x1024.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="800" />\r\n<h4>Resource One Sheets</h4>\r\nA template that lists all relevant contact information for each resource category.\r\n[/image_block]\r\n<h3>Design Solutions</h3>\r\nThe unique challenge to this project was designing templates using Adobe InDesign but then making those template accessible to users who do not use InDesign regularly and go not have a background in design. I learned that CHH uses Adobe Acrobat which has excellent capability with InDesign. By exporting the templates as an <em>interactive PDF</em>, any RSC may copy the template PDF and edit the image and text content while maintain consistency across the branding.\r\n<h4>Deliverables</h4>\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-49" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE_Resident-Services-poster_11x17.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h4>general Resident Services poster</h4>\r\nIn addition to the five collateral templates Ashwin provided me, we proposed to design a large format poster to use to advertise to residents. We proposed to mount these on community boards in public building spaces, around the building property, and will be used primarily to inform residents of the services available. It also supported resident place-making; by giving the CHH property a uniform image, residents are projected to understand the network of support provided by CHH and RSC\'s.\r\n\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-50" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE_resource-one-sheet_8.5x11.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h4>Resource One Sheet Template</h4>\r\nThe template is very similar to the original template. From the beginning I worked out a typographic system and grid layout that is adaptable to each collateral template created. This one sheet example is the simplest form of typography and grid layout used across all the templates.\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-53" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE-calendar_11x8.5.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h4>calendar template</h4>\r\nspecific to each RSC and property\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-51" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE_welcome-sheetgeneral_8.5x11.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h4>building welcome template</h4>\r\ngiven to new residents to make them aware of the Resident Services available upon request\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-52" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE_welcome-sheetJoeyG_8.5x11.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h4>persona template for each RSC</h4>\r\ngiven to new residents in a move in packet\r\n[/image_block]\r\n\r\n[image_block]\r\n[scroller]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-48" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE_event-poster_8.5x11.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-47" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/BLANK_event-flyer_x2_5.5x8.5.jpg" alt="" />[/scroller]\r\n<h4>event ad templates</h4>\r\nused for a variety of community events and workshops; key variables included recurrent events and event sign ups\r\n[/image_block]\r\n<h3>The Impact</h3>\r\nThe general response from the CHH Resident Service Coordinators was positive.\r\n<h3>Successes &amp; Failures</h3>\r\nIn our first meeting, Ashwin noted that the RSC’s primary means of communicating with residents is through community board postings and door-to-door tactics.', 'Capitol Hill Housing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-06-30 02:01:30', '2018-06-30 02:01:30', '', 23, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
