al content to the footer, specific to each RSC and property. This allowed each RSC to put their contact information and the building information on the calendar.\r\n<h4>Building Welcome Template</h4>\r\nThe general  building welcome sheet is given to new residents and includes a welcoming message, important contact information, and more detailed information along a sidebar.\r\n<h4>Welcome Home, RSC Persona Template</h4>\r\nThe RSC persona template is similar to the building welcome template. It is also given to new residents in a move in packet, and contains an inviting introduction plus essential contact information.\r\n<h4>Event Ad Templates</h4>\r\nThe event templates are used for a variety of community events and workshops. Consequentially, I designed a variable sidebar layout for things like recurrent event dates and event sign ups. RSC\'s are able to choose between having a single event data or multiple recurring events. Additionally, there is an option for a sign-up content block with a variable height allowing for more or less sign-up lines.\r\n\r\nI also made a print-off half-sheet event template that synthesizes event information to its primary message and call to action.\r\n<h3>Design Impact</h3>\r\nThe general response from the CHH Resident Service Coordinators was positive.\r\n<h3>Successes &amp; Failures</h3>\r\nAccording to the 2016 CHH annual resident survey, less than half all residents in CHH properties are aware that CHH provides individualize support through their Resident Services program. With this in mind, the primary goal was to design content that informed residents of their Resident Services Coordinators and the Resident Services available through CHH. In order to achieve this, I thought strategically about the visual design and the delivery methods to optimize the RSC\'s collateral rebrand impact.\r\n<h4>Visual Design</h4>\r\nCHH manages about 50 separate properties each with individual eligibility requirements that support a range of residents from, low-income, elderly, disabled, veterans, and other eligibility restricted units. The potential viewing audience for this project spans generations of experience and understand. Given this, I did not want the visual content to distract at all from the text content. More importantly, the text content needed to be simplified to its critical points and written in a way that is accessible to the diverse audience. <strong>(Did I succeed?)</strong>\r\n<h4>Delivery Methods</h4>\r\nThe RS Coordinator\'s primary means of communication with property residents is through information sheets and advertisements given out at CHH offices, community boards in public building spaces on CHH properties, door-to-door tactics and community building events, and through one on one contact with RSC\'s.', 'Capitol Hill Housing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-06-30 03:43:58', '2018-06-30 03:43:58', '', 23, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
