f events and workshops. For maximum ease of use and flexibility, I designed a variable sidebar layout for things like recurrent event dates and event sign-ups. RSCs can choose between having a single event date or multiple recurring events. Additionally, there is an option for a sign-up content block with a variable height, allowing for maximum customization. I also created a half-sheet event template that reduces event information to its hook, a primary message and call to action, for use by the RSC as handouts for local, building specific events.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">[/image_block]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">[image_block]</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">[scroller]<img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-50" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/SAMPLE_resource-one-sheet_8.5x11-791x1024.jpg" alt="" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-36" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/tmpl_resource-one-sheet-e1530319531779-819x1024.jpg" alt="" />[/scroller]</span>\r\n<h4><b>Resource One Sheets</b></h4>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">One sheets are a template that list all relevant contact information for each resource category. I created a typographic system and grid layout that adapts to each collateral template. The system I conceived maintains the appropriate balance between text legibility and readability. This one sheet example is the simplest form of typography and grid layout utilized across every template.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">[/image_block]</span>\r\n<h3><b>Design Process</b></h3>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In developing the collateral pieces, the challenges and goals of the client were kept in the forefront. As such, in all steps of the project development the following were considered: awareness and consistency; accessibility; and usability.</span>\r\n\r\n[column_wrap count="3"]\r\n\r\n[column]\r\n<h4><b>Awareness &amp; Consistency</b></h4>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Consistency affects people’s awareness and trust of a brand. If residents aren’t clear what the RSC provide and who they are in relation to CHH, then they are likely to have less faith in the services provided. I directly addressed this issue through a systematically implemented visual design. Through use of typography, white space, graphic elements and color, I achieved overall visual consistency between each collateral template.</span>\r\n\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<h4><b>Accessibility</b></h4>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The visual design compliments the content strategy and does not detract from it. We simplified the text and used language understood by a general audience. I also utilized a relatively large font size to improve legibility for residents with visual impairments. Attention was also paid to color usage, to increase accessibility for color visually impaired people.</span>\r\n\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<h4><b>Usability</b></h4>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To provide maximum ease of use for the RSC, who may not have a background in design or layout programs, I chose Adobe InDesign to make the templates. The Adobe InDesign has excellent interface with Adobe Acrobat, the program used by the majority of CHH employees. This has resulted in great ease of use for the RSC, allowing for editable content while maintaining overall brand consistency and increased design awareness.</span>\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[/column_wrap]\r\n<h3><b>Project Results</b></h3>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The overall response from the Client, CHH employees, Resident Service Coordinators and residents was overwhelming positive. The visual design and functionality of my project deliverables exceeded their expectations. In fact, after using the new templates, several RSC requested more variations for the event flyers, resulting in additional project work. In recreating these design pieces for CHH, I created a visual design similar enough to the existing look to maintain the familiarity of the old styles, while drastically improving brand accessibility, functionality, consistency and awareness. Our focus on content strategy, language and visual harmony allowed the simple style to accommodate the diverse audiences with propriety and appeal.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">[scroller]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-71" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/IMG_3094_small.jpg" alt="Capitol Hill Housing community event" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-90" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/IMG_2666-768x1024.jpg" alt="" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-89" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/IMG_2499-1024x768.jpg" alt="" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-70" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CAPHILLHOUSING-186-1-1024x683.jpg" alt="Ashwin Warrior enters the Capitol Hill Housing offices on 12th Ave." />[/scroller]</span>', 'Capitol Hill Housing Resident Services', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-07 02:35:56', '2018-07-07 02:35:56', '', 23, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
