(210, 1, '2018-07-07 05:00:07', '2018-07-07 05:00:07', 'I am a reliable digital designer who learns fast and enjoys organization. I excel at composing and formulating information into clear visuals that demonstrate mature application of design theory and practice. With a diverse background in digital and print design, I work with local businesses to develop impact driven collateral including marketing tools, brand identity, templates, website design, presentations and visual strategies.\r\n\r\nMy experience working with a startup, an architecture studio, designing for Seattle businesses, and serving on a 501(c)(3) board as the Design and Marketing Chair, allowed me the opportunity to gain in depth knowledge about the professional and creative sides of design.\r\nPeople tell me I am good at\r\n<h4>Asking Questions</h4>\r\nMy process is driven by curiosity. I address challenges creatively by asking questions first. Afterwards, I thoroughly research target markets, audience demographics, typography and design patterns. At the same time, hand sketching and photographic moodboards compliment my research. This part of my process inspires further conceptual development and helps me understand the variables involved — to properly execute a visual strategy that achieves the project goals.\r\n<h4>Iteration &amp; Variation</h4>\r\nI use an iterative design process to explore many design concepts. Team critiques are an important component to iteration. It opens up dialogue between the design concept and its stakeholders. Brainstorming is another tactic I utilize in my workflow to help teams visual and orient towards a central vision. These conversations inform my process and serve further conceptual development.\r\n<h4>Organization</h4>\r\nWhether it’s my desk space, a quarterly marketing plan, or comprehensive designs, I maintain an organized workspace and accessible workflow. I try to adapt my design process to new variables and maintain an organized workspace. This enables me to simplify the process for clients and provide them with resources that support team goals.\r\n\r\n[column_wrap count="2"] [column class="full"]\r\n<h3>I am confident working in</h3>\r\n[/column] [column]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Industry Knowledge</li>\r\n 	<li>Branding design and positioning</li>\r\n 	<li>Visual design for print and digital media</li>\r\n 	<li>Marketing advertisements and campaign design</li>\r\n 	<li>Social media marketing and website SEO</li>\r\n 	<li>Typography and calligraphy</li>\r\n 	<li>Photography and video editing</li>\r\n 	<li>Brand and Project Management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/column] [column]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Tools &amp; Languages</li>\r\n 	<li>Microsoft Office (Word and Excel)</li>\r\n 	<li>Adobe Creative Suite (InDesign, Photoshop, Illustrator)</li>\r\n 	<li>HTML5 and CSS3</li>\r\n 	<li>Javascript and jQuery</li>\r\n 	<li>PHP Wordpress Development</li>\r\n 	<li>Google Analytics</li>\r\n 	<li>Search Engine Optimization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/column] [/column_wrap]', 'about me', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-07 05:00:07', '2018-07-07 05:00:07', '', 9, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
