y partners and asked them to display and or sell them within their business.\r\n\r\nDigital assets, like neighborhood photographs and Facebook cover photos, expanded the CH Arts District presence online. Additionally, the hashtags #NowEntering and #CapitolHillArtsDistrict were applied to the collateral to track the conversation online.\r\n<h3>Design Solution</h3>\r\nThe Capitol Hill Arts District requested that we deliver to them each the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>11x17 in. poster design</li>\r\n 	<li>6x4 in. postcard design</li>\r\n 	<li>4x4 in. round sticker</li>\r\n 	<li>Facebook cover photo</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n[scroller bg-color="white"]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-mockup-side-by-side.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-225" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-telephone-pole-01.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-226" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-telephone-pole-02.jpg" alt="" />[/scroller]\r\n\r\n[scroller bg-color="white"]<img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_postcards-front-01.jpg" alt="" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223" /><img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_postcards-back.jpg" alt="" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-222" />[/scroller]\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-220" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/Capitol-Hill-Arts-District-social-media-mockup.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<h3>Design Process</h3>\r\nAs the Design Team Lead, it was my responsibility to understand the scope of work to be done, coordinate a schedule between the designers and our client, delegate tasks to each team member, and maintain a positive focus on the project goals and deliverables.\r\n\r\nFirst, we got together and brainstormed the idea to use the collateral advertisements to expand the CH Arts District wayfinding signage. One weekend, I spent the day walking around Capitol Hill and captured over 50 photos of public artworks and murals within the Arts District perimeter. Then, our team regrouped and critiqued initial sketches and define our concept more.\r\n\r\nWith the community photographs to use as the background content for the postcard and poster, Alicia and I produced a series of poster layouts; while Ivy designed the stickers. Alicia went ahead and made the postcard layout. I used the photographs to create social media cover photos. Once again, we regrouped and critiqued our team concept, before further refining the details and presenting to the client.\r\n\r\nAfter the final designs were selected by the client, I thoroughly researched local printers and advertisement companies in Capitol Hill to coordinate getting price estimates, printing the collateral, and posting the flyers. I then put everything together into a single presentation the give to the Arts District Steering Committee.\r\n<h3>Project Impact</h3>\r\nIn March 2017, our team presented the campaign to the Arts District Steering Committee during one of their weekly meetings and recommended a course of action for marketing the CH Arts District.\r\n\r\nThe committee response was overwhelmingly positive. They appreciate the versatility of the design system we made. The text content was minimal and remained consistent across the collateral. The CH Arts District logo was prominently feature like they requested, while the interchangeable background photos of CH Arts District murals highlighted the local community.\r\n\r\nThis design system delivered more value because, since the background content is interchangeable, it empowered the committee to swap out photographs with other options we provided, or even to source background photos from district partners and community members. This was a unique approach to the steering committee and they appreciated the adaptability we provided them.\r\n\r\nThe marketing collateral served as advertisements and aided wayfinding. The large format posters were put along the perimeter of the district to identify its boundary, while small collateral items were used inside partner buildings to allow them to associate with the Arts District. The collateral did a solid job notifying people they were entering a new city neighborhood and complemented existing CH Arts District brand signage. The content was focused and clearly promoted shared art and cultural values, which improved people\'s awareness and perception of the CH Arts District.\r\n\r\nOne issue was, the advertisements were posting these on street poles and our design had to compete with local musicians and community event posters. We combated this issue by reducing the text content to its primary elements and adding ample emphasis to the header. The variety of background photos, taken from the local community, gave the poster design a sense of familiarity because much of the featured artwork was iconic for the Capitol Hill Arts District Community.\r\n\r\nIn combination with branded stickers and postcards, we anticipated that residents would interact with CH Arts District collateral as they enter the neighborhood perimeter, then within community partner locations, and begin to associate the partner location with the CH Arts District.\r\n\r\nTo our excitement, many businesses endorsed our efforts to market the CH Arts District. They liked having the responsibility as a community partners to facilitate the neighborhood’s brand and promote community art engagement. Some community partners even opted to put the poster advertisement in their window, too. After all the CH Arts District would not exist if it were not for the nearly 50 neighborhood partners who make up the Capitol Hill Arts District.\r\n\r\nThe committee accepted our proposed marketing plan and the posters, stickers, and postcards were successfully promoted in the Capitol Hill Arts District throughout the summer of 2017.\r\n\r\n<h3>Sources</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="http://capitolhillarts.org/now-entering/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Capitol Hill Arts, Now Entering campaign</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;" href="https://segd.org/what-wayfinding" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Seattle Environmental Graphic Design: What is Wayfinding?</a></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Capitol Hill Arts District', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '217-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-07 05:21:38', '2018-07-07 05:21:38', '', 217, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/217-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
