he forefront of my process while designing the collateral. During each step of the project, the following were considered: consistency; accessibility; and usability.\n<h4>Consistency</h4>Consistency affects people’s awareness and trust of a brand. If residents aren’t clear what the RSC provide and who they are in relation to CHH, then they are likely to have less faith in the services provided. I directly addressed this issue through a systematically implemented visual design. Through use of typography, white space, graphic elements and color, I achieved overall visual consistency between all collateral templates.\n<h4>Accessibility</h4>The visual design compliments the content strategy and does not detract from it. We simplified the text and used language understood by a general audience. I also utilized a relatively large font size to improve legibility and tested the color contrast, to ensure residents with visual impairments could view the content.\n<h4>Usability</h4>To provide maximum ease of use for the RSC, who may not have a background in design or layout programs, I chose Adobe InDesign to make the templates. The Adobe InDesign has excellent interface with Adobe Acrobat, a program used by the majority of CHH employees. This resulted in great ease of use for the RSC, allowing for editable content while maintaining overall brand consistency.\n<h3>Project Results</h3>The overall response from the Client, CHH employees, Resident Service Coordinators and residents was overwhelmingly positive. The visual design and functionality of my project deliverables exceeded their expectations. In fact, after using the new templates, several RSC requested more variations for the event flyers, resulting in additional project work.\n\nWhile redesigning the RSC collateral, I created a visual design inspired by the existing CHH brand. It maintained the familiarity of the old styles, while drastically improving RSC brand accessibility, usability, and consistency. Our focus on content strategy, language and visual harmony allowed the collateral to accommodate the diverse audiences with propriety and appeal.\n\n[scroller]\n<img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/IMG_3094_small.jpg" class="alignnone wp-image-71 size-full" alt="Capitol Hill Housing community event"><img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/IMG_2666-768x1024.jpg" class="alignnone wp-image-90 size-large" width="360" height="360" alt=""><img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/IMG_2499-1024x768.jpg" class="alignnone wp-image-89 size-large" width="360" height="360" alt=""><img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CAPHILLHOUSING-186-1-1024x683.jpg" class="alignnone wp-image-70 size-large" width="360" height="360" alt="Ashwin Warrior enters the Capitol Hill Housing offices on 12th Ave.">[/scroller]', 'Capitol Hill Housing Resident Services', 'The Capitol Hill Housing Resident Services department needed some brand collateral redesign, in response to many residents indicating they are unaware of Resident Services Coordinators and the resources they provide.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-09 23:56:56', '2018-07-09 23:56:56', '', 23, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
