(291, 1, '2018-07-09 23:58:39', '2018-07-09 23:58:39', 'I was one of three freelance designers retained by local restaurant owner Kevin Chung to develop brand identity and menu signage for his new restaurant Cheese Meats Bread (CMB) in 2017.\n<h3>Background</h3>A colleague Chris Mercurio leveraged his relationship with Kevin to retain a brand design contract and manage the client relationship. He contracted fellow designer, Kenzie Nicholson, and I to execute the brand design. Kenzie and I collaboratively envisioned a brand identity; developed a handout menu, large format menu and food packaging for CMB’s grand opening.\n<h3>Project Challenges &amp; Goals</h3>Cheese Meats Bread is an international take on an american classic—the grilled cheese sandwich. Mr. Chung planned to open in the Uwajimaya Village marketplace in the International District.\n<h3>Design Strategy</h3>During the research phase Kenzie and I talked largely about how to add an international flare to an American classic without having the brand be offensive or too intrusive for a largely international audience.\n<h3>Design Solution</h3>Kenzie and I worked collaboratively throughout the project brainstorming, concept development, and refinement phases. When executing the final deliverables, kenzie created the typographic pattern and packaging design, while I focused on the large format menu board, small take-out menu, and brand identity style guide.\n\n[image_block][scroller]<img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CMB_style-guide_8.5x11.jpg" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-185" alt=""><img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CMB-menu_6x11.jpg" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-188" alt=""><img src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CMB_menu-board_6x4ft_opt-2.jpg" class="alignnone wp-image-187 size-full" alt="">[/scroller]\n<h4>Brand style guide</h4>\n<h4>6x11 in. takeout menu</h4>\n<h4>6x4 ft. menu board</h4>[/image_block]\n<h3>Design Process</h3>While brainstorming and exploring concepts, Kenzie and I provided the client with numerous concepts, each of which approached the CMB brand from a unique lens. Upon listening more closely to general feedback from others and the client’s reaction to our presentation, they liked the variety of font selections we provided, but overall they gravitated towards more simpler fonts and cleaner illustrations. We decided on a typographic solution that used a simple logo mark and a typographic pattern as the primary brand elements, with a gooey yellow accent color—<em>Yumm!</em>\n<h3>Project Impact</h3>We successfully delivered the brand identity packet to the client on schedule and within our budget. Afterwards, I maintained a positive relationship with the client and both design colleagues. CMB is open today and thriving in Seattle’s International District at the Uwajimaya Village market place.\n<h3>Sources</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href="https://cheesemeatsbread.life/">Cheese Meats Bread</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chriselvis/">Client Relations: Chris Mercurio</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kenzie-nicholson/">Designer: Kenzie Nicholson</a></li>\n</ul>', 'Cheese Meats Bread', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-09 23:58:39', '2018-07-09 23:58:39', '', 183, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/183-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
