(315, 1, '2018-07-11 02:48:30', '2018-07-11 02:48:30', '<h3>Background</h3>\r\nFor a service learning assignment, I formed a design team with colleagues, Alicia Smith and Ivy Ye. We partnered with the Capitol Hill Arts District (CH Arts District) to design an awareness campaign that coincided with their new website.\r\n<h3>Project Challenges &amp; Goals</h3>\r\nAccording to a recent neighborhood survey, the majority of residents were unaware that Capitol Hill Arts District exists. It was the first neighborhood to be named as part of the Arts &amp; Cultural Districts program by the Seattle City Government (2014). CH Arts District launched their new website in 2017 to elevate its presence. My team’s primary goal was to build off the visual tone established on their website and to increase local community’s awareness of the CH Arts District.\r\n\r\nAnother key challenge for this design assignment was to manage, plan, and coordinate a collaborative design with a team. As the Design Team Lead, I worked closely with Alicia and Ivy to delegate and deliver to our client a comprehensive collateral design and marketing plan.\r\n<h3>Design Strategy</h3>\r\nOur team collaboratively wrote and developed an original marketing campaign. We focused on the environmental and neighborhood aspect of the CH Arts District by designing the marketing collateral as elements of a wayfinding system—to compliment pre-existing brand elements.\r\n\r\nFor example, CH Arts District recently installed new road signs that include their logo on the District perimeter. This improved drivers’ awareness of the Arts District brand and geographic location. We capitalize on their approach buy advertising the large format posters along the perimeter. This expanded the wayfinding signage for pedestrians and increase people’s perception of the CH Arts District physical boundary.\r\n\r\nInside of the CH Arts District, we empowered community partners to facilitate the neighborhood brand. We distributed small format postcards and stickers to community partners and asked them to display and sell them within their business.\r\n\r\nDigital assets, like neighborhood photographs and Facebook cover photos, expanded the CH Arts District presence online. Additionally, the hashtags #NowEntering and #CapitolHillArtsDistrict were applied to the collateral to track the conversation online.\r\n<h3>Design Solution</h3>\r\nThe Capitol Hill Arts District requested that we deliver to them each the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>11x17 in. poster design</li>\r\n 	<li>6x4 in. postcard design</li>\r\n 	<li>4x4 in. round sticker</li>\r\n 	<li>Facebook cover photo</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[scroller bg-color="white"]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-mockup-side-by-side.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone wp-image-225 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-telephone-pole-01.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-226" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-telephone-pole-02.jpg" alt="" />[/scroller]\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-220 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/Capitol-Hill-Arts-District-social-media-mockup.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h3>Design Process</h3>\r\nAs the Design Team Lead, it was my responsibility to understand the scope of work to be done, coordinate a schedule between the designers and our client, delegate tasks to each team member, and maintain a positive focus on the project goals and deliverables.\r\n\r\nThe design process included reviewing existing collateral and advertisements, and brainstorming ways to expand up the existing wayfinding signage. Utilizing over 50 photos of public artworks and murals within the Arts district, our team developed initial sketches and defined our concept. Next, we developed the postcard and poster content and produced a series of layouts and sticker designs. The photographs were also used to create social media cover photos. We presented refined concepts to the client for final design edits and then approval.\r\n\r\nThe project scope also included researching of local printers and advertisement companies, coordinating and securing price estimates for printing the collateral and posting flyers around Capitol Hill. Lastly, we presented our marketing campaign design to the Arts District Steering Committee.\r\n<h3>Project Impact</h3>\r\nOur team presented the campaign to the Arts District Steering Committee and recommended a course of action for marketing the CH Arts District. The committee response was overwhelmingly positive.\r\n\r\nThey appreciate the versatility of the design system we made. The text content was minimal and remained consistent across the collateral. The CH Arts District logo was prominently featured, as they requested; while the interchangeable background photos of CH Arts District murals highlighted the local community. The interchangeable backgrounds empowered the committee to swap out photographs with other options we provided. We even proposed to source background photos from district partners and community members to delivered more community value. This was a unique approach to the and CH Arts District committee appreciated the variety and adaptability we provided them.\r\n\r\nThe marketing collateral served as advertisements and aided wayfinding. The large format posters were put along the perimeter of the district to identify its boundary, while personal collateral items were used inside partner locations. The collateral did a solid job notifying people they were entering a new city neighborhood and complemented existing CH Arts District brand signage.\r\n\r\nPostcards and stickers provided and interact marketing tactic that improved peoples perception and engagement with the CH Arts District. In addition, the content was focused and clearly promoted shared art and cultural values. By diversifying the type of collateral and the locations they were marketed, it allowed more audience touch points to increase the campaigns impact.\r\n\r\nTo our excitement, many businesses endorsed our efforts to market the CH Arts District. They liked having the responsibility as a community partner to facilitate the neighborhood’s brand. Some community partners even opted to put the poster advertisement in their window.\r\n\r\nThe committee accepted our proposed marketing plan and the posters, stickers, and postcards were successfully promoted in the Capitol Hill Arts District throughout the summer of 2017.\r\n<h3>Sources</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="http://capitolhillarts.org/now-entering/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Capitol Hill Arts, Now Entering campaign page</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://segd.org/what-wayfinding/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">What is Wayfinding? — Seattle Environmental Graphic Design</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[column_wrap count="2"]\r\n\r\n[column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-223 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_postcards-front-01.jpg" alt="" />\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column]\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-222 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_postcards-back.jpg" alt="" width="2812" height="2824" />\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[/column_wrap]\r\n\r\n[column_wrap count="9"]\r\n[column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-234 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-dark-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-227 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-1-red-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-228 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-2-orange-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-229 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-3-yellow-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-230 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-4-green-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-231 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-5-teal-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-232 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-6-blue-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-233 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-7-purple-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column][column]\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-235 size-thumbnail" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_stickers_4in-light-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="135" height="135" />\r\n[/column]\r\n[/column_wrap]', 'Capitol Hill Arts District', 'As Design Team Lead, some colleagues and I partnered with the Capitol Hill Arts District to design an awareness campaign that coincided with their new website.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '217-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-11 02:48:30', '2018-07-11 02:48:30', '', 217, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/217-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
