esign</li>\r\n 	<li>4x4 in. round sticker</li>\r\n 	<li>Facebook cover photo</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[scroller bg-color="white"]\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-mockup-side-by-side.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone wp-image-225 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-telephone-pole-01.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-226" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/CHAD_poster-telephone-pole-02.jpg" alt="" />[/scroller]\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-220 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/wp-content/uploads/Capitol-Hill-Arts-District-social-media-mockup.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<h3>Design Process</h3>\r\nAs the Team Lead, it was my responsibility to understand the scope of work, coordinate a schedule between the designers and our client, delegate tasks to each team member, and maintain a positive focus on the project goals and deliverables.\r\n\r\nThe design process included reviewing existing collateral and advertisements, and brainstorming ways to expand upon the existing wayfinding signage. Utilizing over 50 photos of public artworks and murals within the Arts district, our team developed initial sketches and defined our concept. Next, we developed the postcard and poster content and produced a series of layouts and sticker designs. The photographs were also used to create social media cover photos. We presented refined concepts to the client for final design edits and then approval.  The project scope also included researching of local printers and advertisement companies, coordinating and securing price estimates for printing and posting flyers around Capitol Hill.\r\n<h3>Project Impact</h3>\r\nOur team presented the campaign to the Arts District Steering Committee and recommended a course of action for marketing CHAD. The 