(346, 1, '2018-07-22 19:40:19', '2018-07-22 19:40:19', '<h2>About</h2>\r\nI am a reliable digital designer who learns fast and enjoys organization. I excel at composing and organizing information into clear visuals that demonstrate mature application of design principles. With a diverse background in digital and print design, I help small businesses develop impact driven collateral including marketing tools, branding assets, templates, presentations and the like.\r\n<h2>Education</h2>\r\n<h3>Bachelor of Arts in Digital Design from Seattle University</h3>\r\n<em>Seattle, WA | September 2012 - Dec. 2017</em>\r\n<h3>Write On Calligraphers, Member</h3>\r\n<em>Seattle, WA | July 2018 - current</em>\r\n<h3>The Society for Calligraphy &amp; Handwriting, Member</h3>\r\n<em>Seattle, WA | July 2017 - current</em>\r\n<h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n<h3>Contract Graphic Designer</h3>\r\n<em>JoeyGrable.com | Seattle, WA | current</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Well researched and passionate freelance designer working locally in Capitol Hill, Seattle, specializing in strategic design services from marketing collateral design to comprehensive brand development.</li>\r\n 	<li>Track record of organized project management, punctual delivery, and creative solutions to design problems that exceed client expectations and within budget constraints.</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience managing, updating and maintaining brand standards, design layout, timeline and contract management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Student Design Exhibition Co-Director — flux</h3>\r\n<em>Seattle University Digital Design 2017 Cohort | October 2016 – May 2017</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Collaboratively envisioned cohort exhibition theme.</li>\r\n 	<li>Managed a cohort of 22 student designers to produce a gallery exhibition and fundraiser.</li>\r\n 	<li>Coordinated a two week long design exhibition; over 200 visitors attended the opening night, and we fundraised over $2,000 for the local non-profit Art with Heart.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="p1">Design &amp; Marketing Board Member</h3>\r\n<em>Seattle University Dance Marathon | October 2015 – May 2017</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Redesigned the Seattle University Dance Marathon brand identity and was recognized by the Miracle Network Dance Marathon regional newsletter.</li>\r\n 	<li>Managed all of Seattle University Dance Marathon’s social media platforms and wrote a cohesive marketing plan for Dance Marathon’s tenth birthday celebration.</li>\r\n 	<li>Achieved over 20% growth on Facebook and Twitter, and over 30% growth on Instagram.</li>\r\n 	<li>Engaged with campus student body by designing and organizing creative marketing campaigns with print and digital collateral.</li>\r\n 	<li>Assisted to collectively fundraise over $140,000 for Seattle Children’s Hospital.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Lead Designer, Fragments issue no. 57 &amp; 58</h3>\r\n<em>Seattle University, Fragments Literary Arts Magazine | September 2015 – March 2017</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Managed a team of digital designers by planning and coordinating brainstorms, work sessions, facilitated design critiques in meetings, and oversaw the production process through to print.</li>\r\n 	<li>Conceived a cohesive style to communicate the magazine’s theme.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Architectural Design Intern</h3>\r\n<em>SDK Atelier | Irvine, CA | Summer 2016</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Created digital color schemes and physical mood boards for clients.</li>\r\n 	<li>Rendered house plan elevations in color with landscape and street scenes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Learned how to plot basic floor plans in AutoCAD.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Digital Designer</h3>\r\n<em>San Onofre Surf Co. | San Clemente, California | July 2013 – September 2016</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Coordinated a successful photoshoot for the Fall 2016 girls clothing line.</li>\r\n 	<li>Created graphics and edited pictures for advertisements, banners, products, and special events.</li>\r\n 	<li>Assisted managing the online system for email, e-commerce sales, product management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Skills</h2>\r\n<h3>Professionalism</h3>\r\nCreative problem solver, precise technical ability, organized, goal oriented, excellent time management, inquisitive, fast learner with diverse creative experience, detail oriented, proficent writer, essential bookkeeping, and a very effective communicator.\r\n<h3>Applications</h3>\r\nAdobe Creative Suite CS6, Microsoft Office, Google Suite, AutoCAD, DSLR photography, video editing.\r\n<h3>Languages</h3>\r\nHTML5, CSS3, PHP5+, jQuery, Google Analytics, Search Engine Optimization\r\n<h2>Technical Courses</h2>\r\n<h3>Seattletters, The 37th International Calligraphy Conference</h3>\r\n<em>Bellingham, WA | July 2018</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Attended a week long conference, took a calligraphy course on "Celtic Hybrids and Gothicized Italic" taught by Denis Brown.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Write on Calligraphers, 35th Annual Letters of Joy Conference</h3>\r\n<em>Shoreline, WA | May 2017</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Attended multiple technical classes on various calligraphy and design methods.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>University of California Irvine</h3>\r\n<em>Winter 2015</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Internet systems architecture and search engine optimization, structural website development and advanced website design.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Saddleback College</h3>\r\n<em>August 2011 – March 2012</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Cinema &amp; television production and video editing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Recognition</h2>\r\n<h3>“10,000 Bibles — Sacred”</h3>\r\n<em>December 2017 – April 2018</em>\r\n\r\nA handmade leather bound book made from five iPhones, with illuminated cover design. Exhibited at Seattle University, USA, and Verona, Italy.\r\n<h3>“#DecadeofDM — Best Overall Campaign”</h3>\r\n<em>July 2017</em>\r\n\r\nAwarded the Best Overall Campaign at the national Miracle Network Dance Marathon Leadership Conference.\r\n<h3>“Seattle University Dance Marathon 2016 Style Guide”</h3>\r\n<em>February 2016</em>\r\n\r\nFeatured in the Miracle Network Dance Marathon Pacific Northwest regional newsletter.\r\n<h3>“無 [mu] scroll” (sumi ink on BFK paper, 24.5” x 42” in.)</h3>\r\n<em>June 2016</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Donated to the Seattle University Student Art Collection, to be on display in the Department for Campus ministry\'s Zen Meditation &amp; Eco Sangha office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>“Sight” (pen and ink, 11”x14” in.)</h3>\r\n<h3>“Composition #7” (balsa wood, 4”x4”x10” in.)</h3>\r\n<em>Fragments magazine, issue no. 57 | Seattle University | May 2016</em>\r\n<h3>“Chautauqua” (pastel on paper, 8.5”x11” in.)</h3>\r\n<em>Fragments magazine, issue no. 55 | Seattle University | May 2014</em>', 'Résumé', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'resume', '', '', '2018-07-22 21:09:47', '2018-07-22 21:09:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/JoeyGrable.com/2018_wp-grunt/?page_id=346', 0, 'page', '', 0),
